X
\{ F_\alpha \}_{\alpha \in \Gamma}
\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} F_{\alpha_i} \neq \emptyset
$$If $\{ F_\alpha \}_{\alpha \in \Gamma}$ is a family of closed sets such that $\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} F_{\alpha_i} \neq \emptyset$ for every enumerable subset of the family then $\bigcap_{\alpha \in \Gamma} F_\alpha \neq \emptyset
$Prove that X is separable. 
X
\{ C_\alpha\}_{\alpha \in \Gamma}
\{ C_{\alpha_i}\}_{i \in \mathbb N}
X\neq\bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} C_{\alpha_i}
x \in X
x \not\in \bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} C_{\alpha_i}
x \in (\bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} C_{\alpha_i})^c
\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} X \setminus C_{\alpha_i}
\{ X \setminus C_\alpha\}_{\alpha \in \Gamma}
\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} X \setminus C_{\alpha_i}\neq \emptyset
\bigcap_{\alpha \in \Gamma} X \setminus C_\alpha= (\bigcup_{\alpha \in \Gamma} X \setminus C_{\alpha})^c=\emptyset
\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} F_{\alpha_i} \neq \emptyset
\bigcap_{\alpha \in \Gamma} F_\alpha=\emptyset
X=(\bigcap_{\alpha \in \Gamma} F_\alpha)^c
\bigcup_{\alpha \in \Gamma} X \setminus F_\alpha
\bigcup_{\alpha \in \Gamma} X \setminus F_\alpha
\bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} X \setminus F_{\alpha_i}
X=\bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} X \setminus F_{\alpha_i}
\emptyset=X^c=(\bigcup_{i \in \mathbb N} X \setminus F_{\alpha_i})^c=\bigcap_{i \in \mathbb N} F_{\alpha_i}
